external_knowledge:
The vaccination effectiveness grade is determined by the following percentile categories:
- 'Very High': 90th percentile or higher;
- 'High': 70th-89th percentile;
- 'Medium': 50th-69th percentile;
- 'Low': 30th-49th percentile;
- 'Very Low': below 30th percentile.

sql:
SELECT county_id, confirmed_cases, new_cases, fatality_rate
FROM covid_statistics
WHERE stat_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
COVID-19 refers to the Coronavirus disease 2019, a global pandemic; 
Confirmed cases are individuals who have tested positive for the disease; 
Deaths refer to fatalities caused by the disease; 
Increases in confirmed cases and deaths are calculated over time, comparing the current numbers with the previous reported numbers.
